metadata.name: Luminary Doll in Retro High Fashion 04
metadata.description:
Shot for V magazine NYC with its creative director Stephen Gan.

These are the dresses created by world famed high-end fashion designers in the 60s and 70s.

The dresses were brought out of the collection archive room by concierge with white gloves.

I tried to make them look as iconic as possible with electrical line effects.

Created in October 2014

------
A Still life photographer born in Kumamoto Prefecture, currently based in Tokyo, Shanghai, New York.

He has worked for a great number of commercial visual designing projects with global leading fashion brands.

With his incomparable sense and expressions to precisely capture the true values of the objects, he effectively appeals the brand concept towards consumers.

With ages of devotions in the field of still life photography and strong passion, he keeps looking for new approaches to achieve aesthetic creations of the next level.
